1
00:00:14,633 --> 00:00:15,633
{\an8}Welcome.

2
00:00:34,167 --> 00:00:35,600
May I help you?

3
00:00:37,267 --> 00:00:39,167
You can bring me this bra.

4
00:00:41,567 --> 00:00:43,633
It's for my allergies.
You know, it's fall.

5
00:00:44,400 --> 00:00:46,067
It's all that ragweed!

6
00:00:46,967 --> 00:00:50,167
Don't worry.
I'll bring you the bra.

7
00:00:57,300 --> 00:00:59,467
DESIGNER MIZUKI NISHIZAWA
DESIGNER FUMIKA IDA

8
00:01:03,433 --> 00:01:07,033
How and when did you come up with
the concept of Story?

9
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:12,800
It was while discussing marketing
with President Nanjo at Emotion.

10
00:01:12,867 --> 00:01:16,600
That's when the term "Story" came up.

11
00:01:16,667 --> 00:01:21,400
So the Story concept was Nanjo's idea?
Is that right?

12
00:01:22,333 --> 00:01:23,967
Well...

13
00:01:24,033 --> 00:01:25,633
we were inspired by her words,

14
00:01:25,700 --> 00:01:27,667
but we made it into what it is today.

15
00:01:27,733 --> 00:01:29,800
Nanjo had nothing to do with it.

16
00:01:29,867 --> 00:01:33,433
Have you parted ways with President Nanjo?

17
00:01:34,233 --> 00:01:36,133
That sounds so final.

18
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:41,500
Story is a new brand,
aimed at a younger generation.

19
00:01:41,567 --> 00:01:43,467
All products have a shelf life,

20
00:01:43,533 --> 00:01:45,400
so it's normal
for new things to come along

21
00:01:45,467 --> 00:01:46,833
with every new generation.

22
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:51,933
It sounds as though you're saying that
Emotion is obsolete.

23
00:02:04,300 --> 00:02:05,833
APPOINTMENTS
9/22/15

24
00:02:10,867 --> 00:02:12,900
EM BY EMOTION TEAM
MIZUKI - FUMIKA - SARUHASHI - HIME

25
00:02:19,300 --> 00:02:20,800
So you actually went there?

26
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:24,033
Yes. A little while ago.

27
00:02:25,133 --> 00:02:26,733
How was it?

28
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:27,800
Can I see?

29
00:02:29,967 --> 00:02:31,633
The store was beautiful.

30
00:02:32,633 --> 00:02:34,500
It was full of customers.

31
00:02:34,567 --> 00:02:35,600
I see.

32
00:02:39,567 --> 00:02:40,567
This is nice.

33
00:02:45,333 --> 00:02:46,767
You should stop looking at this stuff.

34
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:52,267
"We wanted to express
the story inside every woman."

35
00:02:54,333 --> 00:02:55,933
How can they do this?

36
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,767
{\an8}A PRODUCT BY TWO WOMEN
FOR ALL WOMEN

37
00:02:57,833 --> 00:03:00,667
The product, the concept.
It's all Emotion's.

38
00:03:02,300 --> 00:03:04,000
This.

39
00:03:04,067 --> 00:03:05,967
This, this and this!
All of it!

40
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:07,800
Why?

41
00:03:11,667 --> 00:03:13,633
How many magazines did you buy, Mayu?

42
00:03:13,700 --> 00:03:17,667
They never used to run
articles on lingerie,

43
00:03:17,733 --> 00:03:20,667
and now, suddenly,
"All women need a Story."

44
00:03:20,733 --> 00:03:22,233
What's going on?

45
00:03:22,300 --> 00:03:23,600
It's good, isn't it?

46
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:25,800
Let's see. "Story.

47
00:03:25,867 --> 00:03:28,567
It's what's inside a woman that matters."

48
00:03:30,067 --> 00:03:31,067
They got that right.

49
00:03:32,033 --> 00:03:33,167
Boss.

50
00:03:33,233 --> 00:03:35,933
The orders for Ms. Kubo and Ms. Hayashi
are ready.

51
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:38,467
Find out when they're available
for a fitting.

52
00:03:39,967 --> 00:03:40,967
All right.

53
00:03:41,033 --> 00:03:44,367
So, all our orders...

54
00:03:45,333 --> 00:03:46,333
Are done!

55
00:03:48,467 --> 00:03:50,533
Now, I can go rest.

56
00:03:58,767 --> 00:03:59,967
This is good.

57
00:04:00,100 --> 00:04:01,167
Where's it from?

58
00:04:02,067 --> 00:04:03,267
Does that really matter?

59
00:04:03,333 --> 00:04:06,233
Well, someone's in a bad mood.

60
00:04:08,367 --> 00:04:12,167
Why haven't you said anything
about what happened, boss?

61
00:04:12,233 --> 00:04:13,633
It's great!

62
00:04:13,700 --> 00:04:15,333
They're now running
more articles on lingerie.

63
00:04:15,967 --> 00:04:17,767
What do you mean?

64
00:04:17,833 --> 00:04:19,667
They stole everything from us!

65
00:04:20,167 --> 00:04:21,600
Stole what?

66
00:04:22,500 --> 00:04:24,800
Mizuki made those, right?

67
00:04:24,867 --> 00:04:27,767
But it's an exact copy of Emotion's style.

68
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:29,033
That's right.

69
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:31,100
Down to the concept of Story.

70
00:04:31,167 --> 00:04:35,467
Story is not a patented term.

71
00:04:35,533 --> 00:04:38,067
We can just do our own version.

72
00:04:40,300 --> 00:04:43,400
We haven't yet printed
the invitations for the show, have we?

73
00:04:43,467 --> 00:04:45,333
No. It's been on hold.

74
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:47,367
Change the date and have them printed.

75
00:04:50,467 --> 00:04:52,333
The trunk show is still on.

76
00:04:53,767 --> 00:04:54,967
The theme will be...

77
00:04:56,067 --> 00:04:57,367
Story.

78
00:05:01,233 --> 00:05:03,533
Well? There's no time to waste.

79
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:05,067
Let's make it happen.

80
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:09,533
That means I'll have to make
many more items.

81
00:05:11,267 --> 00:05:13,167
I must be in hell!

82
00:05:16,667 --> 00:05:17,733
She's right.

83
00:05:18,633 --> 00:05:21,200
Let's show them who the original is.

84
00:05:22,533 --> 00:05:23,667
We can do it!

85
00:05:23,733 --> 00:05:26,267
We've finalized the plans.

86
00:05:26,333 --> 00:05:27,800
We've purchased the materials.

87
00:05:27,867 --> 00:05:30,100
The models are ready to go!

88
00:05:30,767 --> 00:05:32,100
Let's do this!

89
00:05:33,033 --> 00:05:34,267
Yeah!

90
00:05:47,500 --> 00:05:49,433
We apologize for canceling the order.

91
00:05:50,333 --> 00:05:52,700
We'd be happy to pay the fees.

92
00:05:52,767 --> 00:05:53,967
{\an8}DETAILED INVOICE

93
00:05:54,033 --> 00:05:55,933
{\an8}I'm sorry, but we do have to charge you.

94
00:05:56,733 --> 00:05:59,700
I mean, we have people on the payroll.

95
00:06:00,300 --> 00:06:02,033
Of course.
We understand.

96
00:06:02,100 --> 00:06:03,367
You'll get paid by the end of the month.

97
00:06:06,933 --> 00:06:08,200
Is everything all right?

98
00:06:08,267 --> 00:06:10,367
Don't tell me
the company's going bankrupt.

99
00:06:10,433 --> 00:06:12,333
Of course not.

100
00:06:23,667 --> 00:06:24,733
I'm back.

101
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:26,800
-Welcome back.
-We're glad you're back.

102
00:06:33,567 --> 00:06:34,600
What's going on?

103
00:06:34,667 --> 00:06:36,400
We're moving forward with the trunk show.

104
00:06:37,667 --> 00:06:39,267
The theme will be "Story."

105
00:06:40,433 --> 00:06:41,567
Seriously?

106
00:06:41,633 --> 00:06:42,633
Yes!

107
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:49,333
Here it is.

108
00:06:50,233 --> 00:06:51,733
One hundred and seventy-three copies,
please.

109
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:52,967
Sure.

110
00:06:56,433 --> 00:06:57,967
I submitted the invitations.

111
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,067
I'm meeting up with Sosuke in Ebisu,

112
00:07:07,133 --> 00:07:09,433
and we'll go see
the people in charge of lighting.

113
00:07:11,233 --> 00:07:12,233
Yes.

114
00:07:14,367 --> 00:07:15,567
Bye.

115
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:26,700
Wait! Stop!
Hold on!

116
00:07:29,533 --> 00:07:30,533
Yes?

117
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:32,333
It's dangerous.

118
00:07:34,333 --> 00:07:35,867
What's wrong, young lady?

119
00:07:37,900 --> 00:07:40,267
Are you lost?

120
00:07:40,333 --> 00:07:41,733
Where do you need to go?

121
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:43,033
I'll help you.

122
00:07:53,233 --> 00:07:55,400
Isn't this area interesting?

123
00:07:55,467 --> 00:07:57,833
The shops here have been around forever.

124
00:08:01,100 --> 00:08:04,467
The dorayaki here is delicious!

125
00:08:04,533 --> 00:08:06,433
They're often mentioned on TV.

126
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:11,233
Do you live around here?

127
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:14,400
Yes! Very close to here.

128
00:08:14,467 --> 00:08:17,167
I've been in Ginza for 50 years now.

129
00:08:17,233 --> 00:08:18,900
I'm a walking encyclopedia!

130
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:22,233
We're here.

131
00:08:23,133 --> 00:08:25,867
Here's the yakitori shop
you wanted to go to.

132
00:08:26,767 --> 00:08:28,967
The oyakodon here is delicious!

133
00:08:29,967 --> 00:08:32,200
It shouldn't be too crowded at this time.

134
00:08:32,267 --> 00:08:33,267
Goodbye.

135
00:08:34,167 --> 00:08:35,500
Wait!

136
00:08:36,433 --> 00:08:37,433
What is it?

137
00:08:40,867 --> 00:08:41,933
I'm sorry.

138
00:08:43,067 --> 00:08:44,067
May I?

139
00:08:51,333 --> 00:08:53,167
I feel like a princess.

140
00:08:56,833 --> 00:08:59,300
Thank you very much
for helping me.

141
00:08:59,800 --> 00:09:02,167
Make sure you eat lunch

142
00:09:02,233 --> 00:09:03,833
so that you can get back to work.

143
00:09:04,567 --> 00:09:05,567
Yes!

144
00:09:24,067 --> 00:09:25,233
Three more to go.

145
00:09:38,067 --> 00:09:39,733
It's so beautiful.

146
00:09:45,367 --> 00:09:47,400
{\an8}FOR SARI MACHIDA

147
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:12,367
Call everyone over.

148
00:10:13,300 --> 00:10:14,633
No.

149
00:10:14,700 --> 00:10:15,700
Will you wait a moment?

150
00:10:21,800 --> 00:10:22,800
I understand.

151
00:10:31,667 --> 00:10:33,733
{\an8}TOGASHI LAW FIRM

152
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:45,667
Wait a second.

153
00:10:45,733 --> 00:10:47,433
Can I see that?

154
00:10:49,467 --> 00:10:50,967
"Your new product,

155
00:10:51,033 --> 00:10:53,333
including samples
to be used in your trunk show...

156
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:54,533
LEGAL NOTICE

157
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:59,100
...holds too close a resemblance to
the Vanderbilt's Tokyo brand, Story.

158
00:10:59,167 --> 00:11:03,500
Your company has deemed to be
infringing upon copyrighted material,

159
00:11:03,567 --> 00:11:05,333
including all marketing strategy

160
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:07,733
and promotional items
related to the product."

161
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:11,833
We're being sued?
They can't be serious!

162
00:11:13,333 --> 00:11:15,100
They stole from us!

163
00:11:15,167 --> 00:11:16,733
We'll just turn it back on them!

164
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:18,867
That's right. If that's what they want,

165
00:11:18,933 --> 00:11:21,767
we'll just prove in court
that we came up with it first!

166
00:11:23,433 --> 00:11:24,967
We can't do that.

167
00:11:25,733 --> 00:11:27,133
Why not?

168
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:29,333
The fees are outrageous.

169
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:30,867
The trial could go on forever.

170
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:35,000
And since they went public first,
we'd be at a great disadvantage.

171
00:11:35,067 --> 00:11:37,033
But we were first.

172
00:11:37,100 --> 00:11:40,333
The printing company and the models
can be witnesses.

173
00:11:40,933 --> 00:11:42,433
That may not make for
strong enough evidence.

174
00:11:43,700 --> 00:11:45,200
Then what should we do?

175
00:11:45,267 --> 00:11:47,267
They're offering to settle...

176
00:11:49,967 --> 00:11:51,767
if we stop the trunk show.

177
00:11:53,733 --> 00:11:57,133
So they don't want us to compete with
the same Story.

178
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:59,733
If we force the trial and lose,

179
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:01,767
they'll ask for
exorbitant fees in damages.

180
00:12:01,833 --> 00:12:04,067
If that happens,

181
00:12:04,133 --> 00:12:05,133
Emotion will go bankrupt.

182
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:18,000
The trunk show will have to be canceled.

183
00:12:19,467 --> 00:12:22,800
You've both worked so hard.

184
00:12:23,967 --> 00:12:25,067
Thank you.

185
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:46,533
The trunk show
has unfortunately been canceled

186
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:47,733
due to unforeseen circumstances...

187
00:13:00,167 --> 00:13:01,167
Are you okay?

188
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:06,700
I'm sorry.

189
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:12,900
But I still don't get it.

190
00:13:12,967 --> 00:13:14,233
I can't accept it.

191
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:20,000
Neither Mizuki nor Fumika

192
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:22,867
would do something like this.

193
00:13:28,467 --> 00:13:31,933
Well, you just never know with women.

194
00:13:32,933 --> 00:13:34,100
They're scary creatures.

195
00:13:35,300 --> 00:13:38,833
Even I never suspected them
of conspiring together.

196
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:44,233
So this is what it must feel like.

197
00:13:44,300 --> 00:13:49,467
A guy could think
that he's betraying two women,

198
00:13:49,533 --> 00:13:51,800
when in fact, the women get together

199
00:13:51,867 --> 00:13:54,233
and make sure he gets burned.

200
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:58,533
Why are you joking about this?

201
00:13:58,600 --> 00:14:00,167
Wasn't it funny?

202
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:02,167
Mr. Saruhashi,

203
00:14:02,233 --> 00:14:04,133
you always stand off to the side,

204
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:06,900
as if you're not a part of all this.

205
00:14:06,967 --> 00:14:09,200
But you're just afraid

206
00:14:09,267 --> 00:14:11,300
of having to face challenges
and getting hurt.

207
00:14:11,367 --> 00:14:12,967
You just look away!

208
00:14:13,033 --> 00:14:14,300
Mayu.

209
00:14:14,367 --> 00:14:19,700
I know that you worked
as hard as everyone else did on Em.

210
00:14:19,767 --> 00:14:21,867
It must be upsetting to you too.

211
00:14:23,100 --> 00:14:25,233
You should just admit it.

212
00:14:25,300 --> 00:14:26,833
Don't act like it doesn't affect you!

213
00:14:37,867 --> 00:14:40,667
Just another day at the office.

214
00:15:03,833 --> 00:15:05,233
What do you mean?

215
00:15:05,300 --> 00:15:06,367
You're suing Emotion?

216
00:15:07,167 --> 00:15:08,567
I'm just trying to protect the company.

217
00:15:08,633 --> 00:15:10,100
We won't really go to trial.

218
00:15:10,167 --> 00:15:12,867
Is it to protect Story?

219
00:15:13,467 --> 00:15:14,900
That's exactly right.

220
00:15:16,067 --> 00:15:17,967
The product was a hit,

221
00:15:18,033 --> 00:15:20,600
and sold twice as much as expected
in the first week.

222
00:15:21,833 --> 00:15:24,833
Not only in Ginza, but nationwide.

223
00:15:24,900 --> 00:15:27,800
We want to protect our assets.

224
00:15:29,467 --> 00:15:31,767
This isn't right.

225
00:15:36,533 --> 00:15:39,567
Story originally came from Emotion.

226
00:15:39,633 --> 00:15:42,733
Well, I apologize.

227
00:15:42,800 --> 00:15:44,400
I didn't realize that.

228
00:15:44,467 --> 00:15:46,467
That's a lie.
It was all calculated.

229
00:15:51,900 --> 00:15:53,367
So what if it was?

230
00:15:53,433 --> 00:15:54,767
What will you do about it?

231
00:15:58,300 --> 00:16:00,067
Will you testify

232
00:16:01,900 --> 00:16:04,767
that we, all of us,

233
00:16:05,933 --> 00:16:07,300
stole everything?

234
00:16:14,167 --> 00:16:16,300
<i>We can't go back!</i>

235
00:16:16,367 --> 00:16:17,567
Everything's good, isn't it?

236
00:16:17,633 --> 00:16:19,667
Your daughter's happy, right?

237
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:22,467
She buys all the magazines.

238
00:16:22,533 --> 00:16:24,300
With the little allowance she has.

239
00:16:25,233 --> 00:16:26,400
She's a good girl.

240
00:16:27,700 --> 00:16:29,067
She is.

241
00:16:29,133 --> 00:16:31,267
You designed the concept.

242
00:16:31,333 --> 00:16:33,433
Aren't you happy it's doing so well?

243
00:16:35,367 --> 00:16:36,433
Of course.

244
00:16:37,333 --> 00:16:38,833
But this way of doing things,

245
00:16:39,900 --> 00:16:41,033
it isn't me.

246
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:44,467
Whatever the method,

247
00:16:44,533 --> 00:16:49,067
our current success
is exactly what I dreamed of.

248
00:16:51,633 --> 00:16:53,767
This is what I wanted.

249
00:16:55,133 --> 00:16:58,600
For women all over Japan

250
00:16:58,667 --> 00:17:01,333
to wear what I designed.

251
00:17:02,933 --> 00:17:04,900
So, I have no regrets.

252
00:17:07,100 --> 00:17:10,500
I'm going to push forward with this.

253
00:17:19,133 --> 00:17:21,100
I'm so sorry.

254
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:23,367
Don't worry.

255
00:17:23,433 --> 00:17:24,433
I'll be fine.

256
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:27,433
But still, it's work.

257
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,400
That's true.

258
00:17:29,467 --> 00:17:31,800
I'm disappointed I lost the job.

259
00:17:33,300 --> 00:17:34,300
I'm upset.

260
00:17:35,267 --> 00:17:36,267
But...

261
00:17:37,167 --> 00:17:38,733
I understand how you feel.

262
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:40,267
I do.

263
00:18:12,300 --> 00:18:13,500
Poor girl.

264
00:18:38,033 --> 00:18:39,033
2015 SALE PROJECTIONS

265
00:18:48,033 --> 00:18:51,000
EMPLOYEE COSTS

266
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:09,000
It's already been a month
since we got a new order.

267
00:19:09,067 --> 00:19:12,200
Canceling the show really hurt us.

268
00:19:12,267 --> 00:19:17,033
But even our regular customers
haven't been ordering anything.

269
00:19:17,100 --> 00:19:19,900
Perhaps they all went to Story.

270
00:19:22,367 --> 00:19:23,367
Ouch!

271
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:27,000
I'm sorry.

272
00:19:28,033 --> 00:19:31,667
The last deposits
were from Ms. Hayashi and Ms. Kubo.

273
00:19:33,233 --> 00:19:35,800
We're in a tough spot.

274
00:19:35,867 --> 00:19:39,033
We still owe a debt
from when we launched the Em line.

